<br>
1.)  There are quite a few guilds who are NOT ever going back to Vex Thal and are now in the elemental planes.  Is it unreasonable to make a piece of Magi`Kot + Miragul armor an additional 50+ (or 60+, honestly) pet focus item for those of us who got overlooked by Thall Va Kelun?<br>
<br>
2.)  Pet HP is incredibly underpowered for what you fight.  Even the weakest of AEs on boss fights like <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3017&amp;source=Test" target="top">Mighty Bellow of Flame</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (1500 DD plus stun) on Pyronis the deadly hippie frog absolutely wreck pets.  Pet vs Fennin Ro?  vs Babnoxis the Spider?  vs Ofossaa the Enlightened?  vs Tantisala Jaggedtooth?  Forget it, the pet is nothing but a victim.<br>
<br>
3.)  Pet pushing.  This is a HUGE issue in Water and also very applicable in Air, Fire, and Earth.  All it took was one MT getting sent to zone in Water due to pets pushing the mob into a wall before pets / swarms were banned.  How long did it take from assist?  Three pets and five seconds.  Pets used in air can push Avatars into clerics or push the mob oor.  The juggling act required in fights to avoid nearby adds / additional AEs that have long duration stuns + silence instead of damage require CONSTANT pet attention.  It gets to the point to where you won't be missing that 40-50 DPS per mage because the pets cause so many problems.  Host of the Elements also falls under this category for horrible pushing / MT killing due to them getting summoned out of range of clerics.  There are hardly any fights (2 mobs out of all four planes) where the target could be pinned and HoE could be used safely.<br>
<br>
So, what is a mage without a pet on a boss fight?  Basically, a druid who can't heal but has SCS3 to get that extra nuke or two in before being summoned + quadded for 2785.<br>
<br>
What we can do to fix this:<br>
<br>
A.)  Pet HP need a boost all around.  Even trying to help out vs hall trash, two seconds of lag or inattention versus an enrage means dead fully buffed Jobeker with girdle / swords in any plane clearing to a boss.<br>
<br>
B.)  Pets need to have zero push when attacking mobs.  This is going to be a challenge to do, but it's necessary.  For those few fights where I can actually have a pet survive, the mob in question does something else nasty instead of pure DPS.  I can't put the raid at risk by blowing the positioning and pushing said nastiness into camp or the mob far enough out to where the MT gets summoned out of range.  10 seconds is all it takes to blow a fight.<br>
<br>
Now, what do I expect from this post?  Some input from the folks who are feeling this pain right now, some flames / ignorance by folks just now getting into NToV and think a mob that hits for 900 is scary, and probably some flat out clueless people who are more than likely trolling.<br>
<br>
In closing, try to keep it positive - I'm not asking for level 68 pets that hit for 155 or have 700 DD procs, we just need a tool that is more robust and practical in the environment it's being used in.<br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
