<br>
2. I haven't had any problems with WATER PET pushing mobs in PoWater or elsewhere. Earth pet and air pet though are unusable. Fire of course sucks.<br>
<br>
3. I've also found the pet to be no more vulnerable to AoEs then players. When the AoE is devestating to meeles... it's devastating to the pet too. When meele's have a way to survive the aoes (ducking out between blasts, high resists, getting small heals occassionally [64 pet heal]) I can keep the pet alive too, especially with mend companion and suspend companion (having a backup pet in storage). Worst case is it takes 5 seconds to summon a new pet and 3 seconds to Bo4 him. Because many fights are aggro constrained on my nukes and I have vast stores of extra mana, tossing in an occasional heal or new pet costs me almost nothing. I can't use the excess mana to nuke anyway, since I'd get aggro and dai. For example, I don't see how in the world you'd lose both current and stored pet, with mend companion and effectively mana-free 64 heal, against pyronis. I never have.<br>
<br>
